---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { SITE } from "../consts.js";

const title = "Privacy Policy — Kaomoji";
const description =
  "Kaomoji's privacy policy: no accounts, no ads, no tracking cookies. Cookieless aggregate analytics only; your favourites and recents never leave your device.";
const canonical = new URL("/privacy/", SITE).href;

const jsonld = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "PrivacyPolicy",
  name: title,
  url: canonical,
  isPartOf: { "@type": "WebSite", name: "Kaomoji", url: SITE },
};
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} jsonld={jsonld}>
  <p class="crumbs"><a href="/">Kaomoji</a> › Privacy</p>
  <section class="page-head">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      Kaomoji is built to be private by default. No accounts, no ads, no tracking cookies — and
      nothing we collect is ever tied to you.
    </p>
  </section>

  <div class="prose">
    <h2 class="section-title">The short version</h2>
    <p>
      kaomoji.fyi (and the installable app) is a static website with no login and no advertising.
      We collect no personal information, set no tracking cookies, and never sell or share data.
      The only thing we keep is anonymous, aggregate usage counts — and even those can never be
      linked to you.
    </p>

    <h2 class="section-title">What we don’t collect</h2>
    <p>
      We have no account system, so we never ask for your name, email or any personal detail. We
      set no cookies, use no advertising or cross-site trackers, and never collect anything that
      identifies you, your device or your session.
    </p>

    <h2 class="section-title">Analytics</h2>
    <p>
      To understand how the picker is used and make it better, we keep two kinds of
      privacy-preserving, aggregate analytics:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Page views</strong> via
        <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/web-analytics/" rel="noopener">Cloudflare Web Analytics</a>
        — cookieless, with no fingerprinting and no cross-site tracking.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Anonymous usage events.</strong> When a kaomoji is copied or a search is run, we
        may record just that fact — which glyph, or which search term — as an isolated count.
        These events carry <strong>no cookie, no account, no device or session identifier and no
        IP</strong>, so they can show <em>which kaomoji are popular</em> but can never reveal
        <em>who</em> copied or searched for what. Nothing is, or can be, linked back to you.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="section-title">Data stored on your device</h2>
    <p>
      Your favourites and recents are saved in your browser’s local storage so they’re ready
      next time. This data stays on your device, is never transmitted to us, and you can clear
      it any time — by using the “Clear” buttons in the picker, or by clearing your browser’s
      site data. Uninstalling the app removes it too.
    </p>

    <h2 class="section-title">Permissions</h2>
    <p>
      The app uses your clipboard only when you tap a face to copy it. It does not read your
      clipboard, access your contacts, camera, microphone or location, and works fully offline
      after the first visit.
    </p>

    <h2 class="section-title">Children</h2>
    <p>
      Kaomoji is suitable for all ages. Since we collect no personal data from anyone, we
      collect none from children.
    </p>

    <h2 class="section-title">Changes &amp; contact</h2>
    <p>
      If this policy ever changes, the updated version will be posted here. Kaomoji is free and
      open source under the
      <a href="https://github.com/gfrmin/kaomoji/blob/master/LICENSE" rel="noopener">GNU AGPL-3.0</a>;
      questions can be raised on
      <a href="https://github.com/gfrmin/kaomoji" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>.
    </p>
    <p style="color:var(--ink-dim);font-size:.9em">Last updated: 31 May 2026.</p>

    <p style="margin-top:18px"><a href="/about/">About Kaomoji</a> · <a href="/">← Back to the picker</a></p>
  </div>
</Layout>
